\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.2}{\ignorespaces $\varphi $-divergences through density ratios. The left panel shows normalized generators for common divergences as functions of $s=\mathrm  {d}\alpha /\mathrm  {d}\beta $; all curves vanish at $s=1$ up to affine normalization. The right panel shows the discrete formula $D_\varphi (a|b)=\DOTSI \sumop \slimits@ _i b_i\varphi (a_i/b_i)$: hollow blue circles encode $b_i$, filled red circles encode $a_i$, the violet curve gives the ratios $a_i/b_i$, and orange lollipops show local KL-type contributions.}}{76}{figure.6.2}\protected@file@percent }
