\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10.1}{\ignorespaces Wasserstein barycenter grids for four corner measures. The left panel uses the one-dimensional formula $Q_{u,v}=\DOTSI \sumop \slimits@ _{i,j}\lambda _{ij}(u,v)Q_{ij}$ for one Gaussian law and three asymmetric two-Gaussian mixtures, and displays densities reconstructed from the averaged quantiles. The right panel computes entropic Wasserstein barycenters on a common pixel grid for the cat, two-disk, cross and clover silhouettes, using the normalized squared ground cost, $\varepsilon =4\cdot 10^{-4}$ and a Sinkhorn tolerance of $5\cdot 10^{-8}$. The barycenters are rendered as density images with values clamped at their $95\%$ quantile rather than by threshold contours. Colors interpolate between the four corners and encode the same bilinear weights in both panels.}}{126}{figure.10.1}\protected@file@percent }
